                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Biography of John is misplaced (<locus target="#17">17</locus>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES4ra174">4ra-174</ref>va). Usually it comes before
                        the Bǝsrāta Yoḥannǝs “The Gospel of John”.</note>
                     <note>- The “Tituli” for the Gospels of Mark and John are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>- There are 44 “Tituli” for the Gospel of Mark (usually 48) and 19 for
                        the Gospel of John (usually 20).</note>
                     <note>- The canon tables are missing.</note>
                     <note>- The scribe always uses a line break after the number of the chapter
                        before its incipit.</note>
                  </msItem>
