                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">The note is written in Amharic. It is dated to 1936
                              A.M. and concerns a sale of a piece of land in Čäḥat by wayzaro Tǝʾbe
                              ʾAbadi to bašay ʾAsgädom ʾAbḥa for 30 Bǝrr. Below the note, 6
                              fingerprints in purple ink: the seller, the buyer and
                              witnesses.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#132va">f. 132va</locus>
                           <desc>:  Reconciliation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The note is written in Amharic. It concerns
                           reconciliation between two families: the family of blatta Nǝguśe Gäbray,
