                     <origDate notBefore="1667" notAfter="1682">Second half of the 17th cent.
                        The Ms. was probably written during the reign of King Yoḥannǝs I (r.
                        1667-82). It was donated to the church Čäḥat Madḫāne ʿĀlam in the time of
                        rās Sǝbḥāt (s. Additio 1).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>
                     ʾAto Walda ʾAragāwi is mentioned as the donor
                     in Additio 1 and in the supplication formula on 3rb.
 Also his family members are mentioned. The first owner of the Ms. was probably King
                     Yoḥannǝs I (r. 1667-82) since his name, his mother’s (?) name ʾƎḫǝtä Krǝstos
                     and his wife’s name Säblä Wängel are mentioned in the headings of the Gospel of
                     Mark (s. 52rb), Luke (81rb) and John (134rb). Probably,
                     their names were also written in the heading of the Mathews Gospel but later
                     erased (3rb) in order to write down the name of
                     the later donor, ʾato Walda ʾAragāwi.
                     Another possibility is that the commissioner of the Ms. only wished to mention
                     the name of the ruler. 
 Later, the Ms. belonged to the church of Mäqdäla
                     Madḫāne ʿĀlam.</provenance></history>
